items.text: qun's wanton noodle is my favorite
Дешевая китайская еда на этом фудкорте, выбор огромный и все вкусно. Ну а главное радуют цены, они по меркам Сингапура (и даже по меркам Бали) ну очень даже приятные!
Try the massive baos that are made by the Mainland Chinese. It's quite unlike our standard fluffy baos...
Tried the fried dumplings as recommended but the skin is rather thick and not really delicious or juicy... 😣
Poy Kee Yong Tau Foo (Y) must try!
makan malem murah meriah..lumayan...yukkk..makan yuukk... murmer nih
Try Ming Fa fish ball. Superrrrr nice!
Don't try the See Sean Rice Stall. Super stingy even take the chilies also must ask whether you eat or not.
Poy Kee YongTauFoo & Tian Jin Fong Kee fried dumplings must-try. Free tissue packs on random tables
Susah na cr nasi
Must try Tonic House's chicken wing w oyster sauce!!
qun's char siew wanton noodle is my favorite!
Must try Yue Ping fried pumpkin cakes in Chinatown market, they started in 1972.
Try selecta's ice cream bar for 1.25 SGD  😋😊 You'll surely ask for more once you've tasted it! 😊We've bought it near the Seven Eleven Store in front of People's Park Complex.
The dimsum from 道记.. Especially siewmai !!!
You can find all food here
Yong tau foo!! yumms
The food court is dirty
Great variety and value for money,  walk around and choose from one of the numerous restaurants,  from noodles and rice to fish or pork; something for everyone
A good selection of local food here!
Yong tau foo, fruit juice with Yakult. Sorry, don't know the stall's names!
Roasted meats. Avoid 116 Shao La Mian #01-1092. All their meats (roasted duck, roasted pork - sio bak, BBQ pork - char siew) were tough to chew. And cold. Soup was salty too!
Chinatown , is really chinatown I been. Even other country also have chinatown, but I'm sure you can't find the feeling like "so chinatown " at others country. Food is so delicious!
Not bad... Like the skin. Not too floury and thickness just nice. Juicy dumplings.
Delicious milk tea for only S$1.80
Cheap and tasty asian food
Try the char siew rice on the row facing MacDonalds. They use charcoal to roast the char siew, nice :)
Choices of foods are variety.
Gotta try Loh Wei Mei
Come here this is MUST TRY!!!!
Don't ever buy sugarcane juice here. It tastes like long gao zui.
Try Yue Ping famous fried pumpkin cake at opposite Chinatown food centre #02-65. It is nice.
Visit shop : FORTUNE WAFFIN!! Is a must try MUFFINN!!!!!
Koo kee yong tow foo mee, menu no 5 with chili is always great!
Try Teochew Ngoh Hiang (潮州五香) stall's homemade fishball!
You know how all food in Singapore is dire? Well, not quite! Hao Ji Fried Prawn Noodle (01-1108) doesn't just serve the best prawn noodly win, the char koay teow is rather Malaysian (KL-level) too!
Pot Kee Tong Tau Foo is good, but a bit arrogant.
Choices of food are variety.
The stall with the longest queue goes to Yong Xiang Xing Tou Fu.
Dumplings, tofu, Szechuan hot pot
Most of the porridge here cannot make it, except maybe the frog leg ones
YTF...Its to die for.If you are still alive after the meal..head to the coffee joint at the corner n try the ice coffee.
Yong Tau Foo is a MUST!!!
Dumplings: Tian Jin Fong Kee #01-1046 apparently has 30-yo history @ this food centre. Hero offerings: steamed & fried dumplings. Smallest order $6 for 12 dumplings. Make sure u hv enuf ppl 2 share w
If u wan sth light n simple.. Try Koo Kee Yong Tow Foo Mee.. Niceee...
Full of tiny little robots queuing up. If you don't try, you lose the game!
Another of many hawker food courts in Singapore. I love their 1000 ways of dumplings
#01-1142 Fruits juice like plain water! Add so much water and ice. Really like "Long Gao Zui"
Don't miss the Hakka yong tau foo!
このストールに異常に長い列だったが、理解していない。時間は日曜日の昼過ぎ。あきらかに話題店だと思われるが、調べていない。
Nice Pig intestine soup n just beside it, there's nice handmade noodle
Go for the food, avoid the toilets.
DIY popiah: Fortune Food #01-1008 sells handmade (actually central kitchen) popiah skin ($15/kg), ground peanuts, crispy bits, chilli sauce, etc to host ur own popiah party @ home. Easy!
Fun spot for coffee, beer, and seafood.
Koo Kee Yong Tau Fu is quite forgettable, there is 1 prawn noodle which is quite bland as well, must try the Ngoh Hiang though
Try the teochew bachor/fishball. Beats anywhere hands down!
Ice Durian Kachang and Fish Ball ... Sluurrpp!!
Don't you dare try their siopao here. It costs 1.5SGD, cheap since it is big and really looks yummy. It has the weirdest taste and smell. 👎 In the end, we were not able to eat it. 😣😔
Hakka Yong Tau Foo - only $2.50 The line was 15 pp strong. Smells divine. Gotta be good.
This hidden corner shop actually taste much better than the famous 日日红麻辣香锅。This Ma-la hotpot is unit #01-1060A
The zhen zhu fang curry mix rice store is nice. The soya pork is killer. Looks sinful but heavenly!
If you want something that will knock your lips out of commission, try out the spicy dishes @ Sichuan Famous Snacks, #01-1044
The la mian stall here hand makes their own noodles! Not bad!
try the Beef/Chicken Pau near Mcdonalds..love it!
The pork-ribs noodle from the shop at #01-1044 is the best !
Try e Dao Ge with Cockerel... Nice 
Level 2 corner @ Swanston - your essential store for your daily use and need... Super cheap and can save up to 50% compare with all skin care store or supermarket... Great value
Yong tau foo: Lots of stalls here. 1 of them, Poy Kee Yong Tau Foo #01-1066, sees daily loyals. Fishball salty but everything else is yummy. Noodles q, chilli sauce kicking!
has one of the best fried gyoza
Braised duck: Fans make a bee line for Lek Kee #01-1104 during mealtimes. Meat cuts r thick & generous, braised sauce has d traditional herbal aroma.
Alway go there eat fried oyster that next to the drink stall, very good!
Keep a lookout for free tissue packs on selected tables.
Fun to see, lots of Chinese, not a lot of tourists. All food is alright here, lots of different kinds.
Fishball noodles: Familiar local brand Ming Fa has a stall here #01-1140 selling fishball & minced meat noodles (bak chor mee). Both delicious. Fishball & meatball bigger than golf balls!
the porridge beside the sugar cane store fail. not hot! -.- oh they sell chicken rice and soup also!
Try the Fishball noodle near Mr Bean stall,generous helping of fish cakes
Nice culinary
Ming Xing Wu Xiang xia bing stall 1118 is my favourite since childhood. Chilli sauce is old school and her fried bee hoon is first class
Local desserts: Only 3 stalls in this massive food centre, all along the same row facing OG. New Happy Cafe #01-1024 scores high in my books, for getting d basic green bean soup right - thick & sweet
Try the porridge and Yong Tau Foo. Is nice. Their chicken rice and hotwoks also not bad.
The roast meat stall near the main road sells the best char siew and duck noodles.
In the evening the place is filled with drunken uncles and everybody seems to be eating huge bowls filled with animal innards. The place has what you call, 'character'. Korean stall 01-1054, not bad.
Must try the 猪什汤 here, it's yummy!!
Must eat Toh Kee roast duck & roast meat. Power!!! #01-1016A
Try the dumplings@tian jin fong kee, the inside outlet! They're super super nice I swear!!(:
Varieties of local hawker foods you can found in here.
Toh kee is the better char siew rice, nearer OG
Fishballs fr Teochew Bakso #01-1008 are big! Fish cake slices r also generous but salty. Best eaten & balanced w plain noodles
Great place to shop for floral prints fabrics - level 2
The Teh O kosong pheng here is really good! For those who are health conscious, can give it a try! 
What a great place to eat good value food and mix with the locals. I love it!
Dim sum: Chop Hean Kuan #01-1018. Stall  does brisk business selling takeaway items during mealtimes. Food items r made fresh 2 doors away :-)
Tian Jin Fong Kee is my favorite fried Gyoza
Beef noodles: Meat was tough & xtra chewy fr Joo Chiat Beef King #01-1064. Well... just d wrong batch :-(
A very MUST for Yong Tau Foo!!!
Corner Ma la hotpot always has a line. I prefer #01-1048 in the middle.
Due to its proximity to China Town, most of the stalls sell Chinese. Easy to miss behind the walls of the market, despite being 10 feet from the MRT exit. Great pig stomach soup!
Go and get the fried pork dumplings from Tian Jin Fong Kee. Golden brown and crispy on the outside, and juicy on the inside
Mixed meat make your own dish at the eastern end is reasonably good.
Dirty tables and chairs and quite stinky
Try the pork rib hor fun. Good stuff.
Do try the Indonesia fried char Kway tiao really nice and a cup of sugarcane to with it
Try the Tian Jin Fong Kee fried dumplings.. Thin skin with lots of filling pan fried till skin is crispy but filling still remains juicy... Yums!!!
the worst place in singapore , the toilet is dirty and no one take care of it
I like the desserts at New Happy Cafe, facing OG.
麻辣香锅超赞的.. 必吃!
高记酿豆腐面！Must try!
Oh no~ I fall in love with their muffins!!! @ Fortune Waffin!!

YI PIN BEEF KING 一品牛腩王 01-1074. Just moved here. Tender mix brisket with tripes and tendons. I love the soup version with kway tiao (flat rice noodles). Always one of my favourites in Chinatown. Best!
